<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>505 Internal Server Error - Oops!</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jquery@3.6.0/dist/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f0f8ff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 50px;
        }
        .error-container {
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #ffcccc;
            border: 2px solid #ff0000;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            animation: shake 0.5s ease-in-out infinite;
        }
        .error-title {
            font-size: 5em;
            color: #ff0000;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .error-message {
            font-size: 1.5em;
            color: #333;
        }
        .back-btn {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 1.2em;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        .back-btn:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }

        @keyframes shake {
            0% { transform: translateX(0); }
            25% { transform: translateX(-10px); }
            50% { transform: translateX(10px); }
            75% { transform: translateX(-10px); }
            100% { transform: translateX(0); }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <div class="error-container">
        <div class="error-title">505</div>
        <div class="error-message">
            <h2>Oops! Something went wrong at the server!</h2>
            <p>Looks like the server is taking a coffee break.</p>
            <p>Don't worry, we're on it. Hang tight!</p>
        </div>
        <button class="back-btn" onclick="window.history.back();">Go Back</button>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    $(document).ready(function() {
        // Optional animation effects when the page loads
        $(".error-container").fadeIn(2000);
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
